{"id":14881813,"mediaExerciseId":"1ff718b4-b720-4217-85a3-1fa5aa4b78d7","exerciseName":"3","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"23.3","sectionTitle":"Hedging with Forward Contracts","pageNumber":772,"solutions":[{"id":5990264,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This question deals with the concept of forward contracts and how companies and firms use these contracts to manage their risk. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**3a.** In the most basic terms, a forward contract is a prior agreement between the seller and the buyer on the price for a certain product.\n\nThis means that there is already an agreed upon price that the buyer will pay in the future regardless of the current value of the product.\n\nIf the product has a higher value on the period of sale, then the buyer will gain. If the product has a lower value, then the buyer will incur a loss. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":218,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/ddbd3ce42723c8e471e8a08d08f75d07/5382c74be2dcd590f74113cc110df53f/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/ddbd3ce42723c8e471e8a08d08f75d07/5382c74be2dcd590f74113cc110df53f/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**3b.** Forward contracts are a great way to alter a company's risk profile since this is an example of hedging where they use trading strategies to try and negate future losses.\n\nIf the value of the product decreases, then the firm will negate the possible loss since the value of the company increases in the forward contract.\n\nOn the other hand, if the product increases, then the company offsets its losses with the gains they made in the forward contract. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":256,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/ddbd3ce42723c8e471e8a08d08f75d07/37c3e32191c067d0b85fbfa94a300acd/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":128,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/ddbd3ce42723c8e471e8a08d08f75d07/37c3e32191c067d0b85fbfa94a300acd/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"1f81f1f0-3839-4afe-9953-62438b356f26","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881814,"exerciseName":"4","page":776,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"1d9d8c6d-d5ea-4663-b822-64cb730a88c7","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-exercises-4-1d9d8c6d-d5ea-4663-b822-64cb730a88c7"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881812,"exerciseName":"2","page":769,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"c36f17cf-fa70-4fb8-b003-85ea9ecc10ad","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-exercises-2-c36f17cf-fa70-4fb8-b003-85ea9ecc10ad"}],"_webUrl":"https://quiz